article.headline: Winthrop 69, VMI 44
article.story: ROCK HILL, S.C. (AP) -- James Shuler scored 15 points as Winthrop beat VMI 69-44 on Monday night. Torrell Martin's 3-pointer started a 15-4 run end of the first half run as the Eagles (16-5, 7-1 Big South Conference) led 34-18 at the break. Winthrop increased its lead to 56-28 before coach Gregg Marshall cleared his bench, letting four freshman and a walk-on play the final eight minutes of the game. The Keydets (5-13, 0-8) tied the game at 4-4, but could never get any closer. The Eagles shot 59 percent (26-of-44) from the field for the game, compared to VMI's 35 percent (16-of-46). Phillip Williams scored 14 points and Otis Daniels added 10 points and seven rebounds for Winthrop. Reggie Williams led the Keydets with 14 points and Tim Allmond added 10.
